WEBVTT

00:01.402 --> 00:03.637
I'm here to celebrate the good
news about my beloved nephew

00:03.671 --> 00:04.538
dating AnnaBeth Nass.

00:04.572 --> 00:05.573
I'm here to warn you.

00:05.606 --> 00:06.640
You came to my house

00:06.674 --> 00:08.042
to tell me
my new boyfriend

00:08.076 --> 00:09.777
is only with me
as part of a plot...

00:09.810 --> 00:11.779
I'm trying to protect you.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.647
You're being
a jealous ex-boyfriend.

00:13.681 --> 00:15.116
GEORGE:
 The sex was amazing.

00:15.149 --> 00:16.417
With Lemon?!
Shh! Shh!

00:16.450 --> 00:18.519
Every time I look at her,
I am physically unable

00:18.552 --> 00:19.553
to stop picturing it.

00:20.788 --> 00:23.457
What's he...?
Charles slept
on the couch.

00:23.491 --> 00:25.426
He stayed here?
It wasn't a big deal.

00:25.459 --> 00:27.561
Okay.
I should go.

00:27.595 --> 00:29.663
Yeah. I'll call you later.

00:47.848 --> 00:50.050
Oh, what the hell.

00:52.486 --> 00:54.722
(beep)

00:54.755 --> 00:56.724
Hi! You've reached
Vivian Wilkes.

00:56.757 --> 00:58.492
Leave a message.

00:58.526 --> 01:00.861
Uh, hey, Viv. It's Wade calling.

01:00.894 --> 01:03.597
Just thought
I'd give you a shout.

01:03.631 --> 01:05.199
Been a few days...
(thudding)

01:07.168 --> 01:09.803
I am gonna wring your little...!

01:09.837 --> 01:12.173
Uh...

01:12.206 --> 01:13.641
not you.

01:13.674 --> 01:14.875
The... the raccoon.

01:14.908 --> 01:16.844
Which-which... may...

01:16.877 --> 01:18.779
May-Maybe that sounded weird,
but there was...

01:18.812 --> 01:20.648
there was a raccoon.

01:20.681 --> 01:22.583
Which you probably guessed.

01:22.616 --> 01:24.852
And, uh, well, now it's gone.

01:24.885 --> 01:26.854
So, uh...

01:26.887 --> 01:28.822
look, I-I'd love to see you.

01:28.856 --> 01:33.194
And there are no more raccoons
over here at Casa de Wade.

01:33.227 --> 01:35.229
Call me.

01:36.230 --> 01:37.598
(beep)

01:37.631 --> 01:39.333
(whispering):
Casa de Wade. What?

01:39.367 --> 01:41.202
LAVON:
 I can't get any lower.

01:41.235 --> 01:43.237
I've sunk as low
 as humanly possible.

01:43.271 --> 01:45.606
Blew our chance
to host the county fair.

01:45.639 --> 01:47.775
A.B. hates me, town hates me.

01:47.808 --> 01:49.510
And, in worse news,

01:49.543 --> 01:51.679
I am the subject
of the Owls' charity roast.

01:51.712 --> 01:53.514
They won't even need
to write jokes.

01:53.547 --> 01:57.318
Come on. I know times are rough,
but you're Lavon Hayes.

01:57.351 --> 01:59.753
Two Super Bowls,
four Pro Bowls.

01:59.787 --> 02:02.656
Every time you get knocked down,
you get right back up. Come on.

02:02.690 --> 02:03.891
Go.

02:03.924 --> 02:05.826
Oh.
Geez.

02:05.859 --> 02:07.895
I did get knocked down a lot.

02:07.928 --> 02:10.231
See, it's a pattern.
No, that's not
what I meant at all.

02:10.264 --> 02:11.265
Oh.

02:11.299 --> 02:12.533
Oh. (sighs)

02:12.566 --> 02:13.734
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where are you going?

02:13.767 --> 02:14.835
I need to talk to you.

02:14.868 --> 02:16.537
LAVON:
Not now.
Owl meeting.

02:16.570 --> 02:18.606
I got to face the
music, the pitchforks,

02:18.639 --> 02:20.241
the rotten tomatoes in my face.

02:20.274 --> 02:21.942
(scoffs)

02:21.975 --> 02:24.245
(laughs)

02:24.278 --> 02:27.815
Wade, everything okay?

02:27.848 --> 02:29.917
Just fine. Dandy.

02:29.950 --> 02:33.654
Yeah? Well, that thinking crease
is making a rare appearance

02:33.687 --> 02:35.789
in your forehead,
so, what's going on?

02:35.823 --> 02:37.791
It's just Vivian.

02:37.825 --> 02:39.593
All right?
Things are, oh,

02:39.627 --> 02:40.761
weird between us.

02:40.794 --> 02:42.663
She's distant, she
won't return my calls.

02:42.696 --> 02:44.665
She's spending a lot
of time with Charles.

02:44.698 --> 02:45.966
So, her and Charles are friends.

02:45.999 --> 02:48.269
It's evolved.
It's great for Harley.

02:48.302 --> 02:50.571
I wish my parents made
that kind of effort.

02:50.604 --> 02:52.340
Trust me, he's not making
that effort for Harley.

02:52.373 --> 02:55.343
Oh, Wade, come on.
Vivian is crazy about you!

02:55.376 --> 02:57.645
And Charles--
he's Charles.

02:57.678 --> 02:59.280
But you-- you're you.

02:59.313 --> 03:01.215
You know?
He's not a threat.

03:01.249 --> 03:02.950
Oh, come on.
No more thinking face.

03:02.983 --> 03:04.952
Look, I'll tell you what.

03:04.985 --> 03:07.388
I have plans with Vivian
to get our nails done later.

03:07.421 --> 03:08.689
I'll do some digging.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.691
You'd do that for me?
Yeah, well, I have to.

03:10.724 --> 03:11.825
I am your doctor.

03:11.859 --> 03:12.960
Besides, all this sudden

03:12.993 --> 03:15.696
thinking could be very dangerous
for your unused brain.

03:15.729 --> 03:16.897
Ha, ha.

03:16.930 --> 03:18.699
Thank you.

03:18.732 --> 03:20.334
Mm-hmm.

03:21.669 --> 03:23.971
George.

03:24.004 --> 03:25.339
(distorted):
George.

03:26.440 --> 03:27.741
(distorted):
Have you seen this report?

03:27.775 --> 03:28.876
(clearly):
What are we gonna do?

03:28.909 --> 03:30.411
Uh...

03:30.444 --> 03:33.314
George! You're
doing it again.

03:33.347 --> 03:34.982
You're zoning out.
No. No. No,
Lemon, I'm not.

03:35.015 --> 03:36.684
I was... I was just...
I was just

03:36.717 --> 03:37.885
really thinking
about what you were saying.

03:37.918 --> 03:40.988
Which was...?
You know, the...

03:41.021 --> 03:42.456
(mutters)
The health
inspection report.

03:42.490 --> 03:43.957
Yeah.
We got an A-minus.

03:43.991 --> 03:45.893
Which is great.
An A-minus, George.

03:45.926 --> 03:48.462
An A-minus!

03:48.496 --> 03:50.898
Mae Ellen Waterloo has never
given me less than an "A,"

03:50.931 --> 03:52.433
not even for the Rammer Jammer.

03:52.466 --> 03:54.335
A glowing and pristine
cleanliness is my signature.

03:54.368 --> 03:55.669
Okay.

03:55.703 --> 03:57.871
Well, then, maybe Mae,
you know, had a bad morning.

03:57.905 --> 04:00.341
She got out of bed on
the wrong side, or someone peed

04:00.374 --> 04:03.043
in her coffee.
Who knows?
Well, not at Fancie's!

04:03.076 --> 04:04.312
That might have happened
at the Rammer Jammer,

04:04.345 --> 04:05.413
but nobody ever knew, so...

04:05.446 --> 04:06.847
I wish I didn't know about it.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.982
George, you're right.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.018
Mae wasn't her usual
bubbly self. She wasn't

04:11.051 --> 04:12.886
whistling or making any jokes.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.788
Exactly. There you go.
Mystery solved.

04:14.822 --> 04:16.023
Now you can just move on.

04:16.055 --> 04:18.959
Or... I can fix her.

04:19.993 --> 04:22.262
Thank you, George.

04:31.038 --> 04:34.041
Good Owls, last week
I let my personal life--

04:34.074 --> 04:35.776
you know, my breakup with A.B.,

04:35.809 --> 04:38.045
my animosity
for all things Gainey--

04:38.078 --> 04:40.848
get in the way
of BlueBell's best interest.

04:40.881 --> 04:42.950
Which is why
I understand if you want

04:42.983 --> 04:45.085
to cancel your annual
Mayoral Toast and Roast.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.855
Better yet, let's
vote on a replacement.

04:47.888 --> 04:49.022
I nominate me.

04:49.056 --> 04:51.058
MAYFAIR:
No! Now, is there

04:51.091 --> 04:53.327
anyone here
who has not crossed the line

04:53.361 --> 04:55.062
when it comes
to matters of the heart?

04:55.095 --> 04:56.464
Hmm? Why,
when I was

04:56.497 --> 04:58.332
in the seventh grade,
I joined the choir

04:58.366 --> 05:00.334
just so I could sit next
to Ella-Jean Swain.

05:00.368 --> 05:01.802
BILL:
It is possible

05:01.835 --> 05:03.704
that I may have let

05:03.737 --> 05:06.440
Cupid's arrow talk me out
of any number of tickets.

05:06.474 --> 05:08.776
Mm.
I sent 150 postcards
to Kerry Washington

05:08.809 --> 05:10.077
and flowers on
her birthday.

05:10.110 --> 05:11.512
All returned.

05:11.545 --> 05:13.547
(crowd murmuring)
Mm. Mayor Hayes,

05:13.581 --> 05:16.550
we, the Owls,
stand by you.

05:16.584 --> 05:18.952
All those in favor
of moving forward

05:18.986 --> 05:20.854
with the Mayoral
Toast and Roast,

05:20.888 --> 05:22.055
let me
hear you hoot.

05:22.089 --> 05:24.024
(all hooting)

05:26.594 --> 05:28.829
Hooty, hoot, hoot, hoot!
(hooting continues)

05:31.865 --> 05:33.967
Belles, I understand
there are some among you

05:34.001 --> 05:36.737
that may take issue
with my new boyfriend.

05:36.770 --> 05:39.940
It is true
that Davis Polk is a Gainey,

05:39.973 --> 05:42.443
but he is also
a wonderful

05:42.476 --> 05:44.011
and honest man.

05:44.044 --> 05:46.880
That said, if you feel
the need to censure me

05:46.914 --> 05:48.916
or even ask for my resignation

05:48.949 --> 05:51.452
as Belle co-leader,
I will not object.

05:51.485 --> 05:52.486
Well, I will.

05:52.520 --> 05:53.587
If AnnaBeth is happy,

05:53.621 --> 05:54.955
then we should be happy

05:54.988 --> 05:56.590
for her.
Agreed.

05:56.624 --> 05:57.925
Seconded and thirded!

05:57.958 --> 05:59.393
Especially after the way

05:59.427 --> 06:01.094
you crapped out
in love this year.

06:01.128 --> 06:02.830
Oops.
Send that to college, Crickett.

06:02.863 --> 06:05.399
What I mean is,
shame on Mayor Hayes!

06:05.433 --> 06:06.400
(overlapping chatter)

06:06.434 --> 06:08.001
He wastes

06:08.035 --> 06:09.870
some of
your most fertile months,

06:09.903 --> 06:12.072
breaks up with you,
and then has the gall

06:12.105 --> 06:13.006
to Gainey-shame you?!

06:13.040 --> 06:15.142
Well, I'm not sure
I would go that far...

06:15.175 --> 06:16.844
That's right, Elodie.

06:16.877 --> 06:18.879
Lavon is the one who
should be censured.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.848
I move that we pull out

06:20.881 --> 06:23.451
of the Owls' Mayoral Toast
and Roast this year

06:23.484 --> 06:26.520
in solidarity
for our beloved A.B.

06:26.554 --> 06:27.821
Oh, I don't know.

06:27.855 --> 06:29.990
I mean, we've rehearsed,
and the costumes

06:30.023 --> 06:30.824
are really great.

06:30.858 --> 06:33.160
But, oh, y'all would do that
for me?

06:33.193 --> 06:33.961
All in favor?

06:33.994 --> 06:34.962
ALL:
Yea!

06:34.995 --> 06:37.898
Yay!

06:40.968 --> 06:42.870
Hey, George.
How are you?
Oh, hey.

06:42.903 --> 06:45.539
Good to see you.
Oh, I'm good.
I'm good. Thank you so much,

06:45.573 --> 06:48.642
Reverend, for taking
the time to see me.

06:48.676 --> 06:50.444
It's much appreciated.
Well,

06:50.478 --> 06:54.081
of course, whenever one of my
flock asks for help, I help.

06:54.114 --> 06:56.016
So, lay it on me, brother.

06:56.049 --> 06:56.950
(laughs)

06:56.984 --> 06:59.052
It's a little too much
vernacular sauce?

06:59.086 --> 07:00.087
No, no, it's-it's...

07:00.120 --> 07:01.121
I'm sorry.
Just a little...

07:01.154 --> 07:02.523
Go ahead.

07:02.556 --> 07:04.925
Uh, but, anyway,
the-the situation is...

07:04.958 --> 07:07.861
You know, say that one
of your flock, uh,

07:07.895 --> 07:10.998
had developed feelings for the

07:11.031 --> 07:14.535
most spoiled, irritating
and annoying sheep in town,

07:14.568 --> 07:18.572
and-and... he wants
to rid himself of said feelings.

07:18.606 --> 07:20.608
George, it sounds
like you need something

07:20.641 --> 07:23.010
to take your mind off
this particular sheep,

07:23.043 --> 07:25.112
and I know
just what it should be.

07:25.145 --> 07:27.047
Prayer.

07:27.080 --> 07:29.550
A date with our visiting
Sunday school teacher.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.218
Oh, yeah. No.

07:31.251 --> 07:34.021
I mean, no offense, Reverend,

07:34.054 --> 07:36.957
but that-that is so not
what I had in mind.

07:36.990 --> 07:38.859
Well, I think
it's a great idea.

07:38.892 --> 07:40.994
And you know who also thinks so?

07:43.263 --> 07:45.098
Big guy in the sky?

07:45.132 --> 07:47.635
That's correct, George.
Big guy in the sky.

07:47.668 --> 07:49.970
Yeah, I was afraid of that.

07:50.003 --> 07:53.140
Yeah, and now that Harley has
gotten a hit in the actual game,

07:53.173 --> 07:55.543
he's telling the coach
to call him Little Papi.

07:55.576 --> 07:57.277
That is so cute.
I know.

07:57.310 --> 08:00.013
How-How's, uh, everything
else going? How's work?

08:00.047 --> 08:01.582
It's good. We're starting
our unit on geology,

08:01.615 --> 08:02.950
which is my favorite
time of year.

08:02.983 --> 08:03.851
That is awesome.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.619
How is Wade? How are
things going there?

08:05.653 --> 08:07.187
Why are you asking?

08:07.220 --> 08:09.122
You don't usually.
Did he say something?

08:09.156 --> 08:10.958
No! No.

08:10.991 --> 08:12.593
Okay, well, he might
have mentioned

08:12.626 --> 08:14.127
that you hadn't
called him back.

08:14.161 --> 08:16.129
Yeah.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.065
I've sort of been
avoiding him.

08:18.098 --> 08:20.067
What? Why?

08:20.100 --> 08:22.636
The other night,
Wade told me

08:22.670 --> 08:24.605
that he thought Charles
was trying to get me back.

08:24.638 --> 08:25.739
So Wade was jealous.

08:25.773 --> 08:27.107
You can't punish
him for that.

08:27.140 --> 08:28.676
But the thing is,
Wade was right.

08:28.709 --> 08:30.744
Charles does want you back?

08:31.945 --> 08:33.581
But what about you?
How do you feel?

08:33.614 --> 08:35.215
Confused.

08:35.248 --> 08:38.318
Charles and I had nearly
15 happy years together.

08:38.351 --> 08:40.621
He's the father
of my child.

08:40.654 --> 08:43.222
But he left,
and now there's Wade, who...

08:43.256 --> 08:44.958
He's amazing, and...

08:44.992 --> 08:46.994
And he cares about you a lot.

08:47.027 --> 08:49.029
I know.

08:49.062 --> 08:51.031
Promise me you won't
tell him, okay?

08:51.064 --> 08:53.033
Okay.

08:53.066 --> 08:54.568
But you have to.

08:54.602 --> 08:56.604
I will.

08:56.637 --> 08:59.139
Just as soon as I decide
what to tell him.

09:02.810 --> 09:05.212
(car horn honks)

09:05.245 --> 09:07.314
(seagulls calling)

09:07.347 --> 09:09.650
(birds singing)

09:18.692 --> 09:20.661
(screams)

09:20.694 --> 09:22.596
Hey, Doc. Just doing a bit
of tree-trimming.

09:22.630 --> 09:23.697
Sorry I scared you.

09:23.731 --> 09:25.198
No, no, not scared.
See you later.

09:25.232 --> 09:26.800
Uh, you know,
I stopped by last night.

09:26.834 --> 09:28.068
You-you didn't answer.

09:28.101 --> 09:29.236
Oh, I fell asleep early.

09:29.269 --> 09:30.704
At 8:30?
Yeah, I was exhausted.

09:30.738 --> 09:31.972
Or you're avoiding me.

09:32.005 --> 09:33.641
What?! Why would I do that?

09:33.674 --> 09:34.574
I don't know.

09:34.608 --> 09:36.977
'Cause Vivian told you something
yesterday.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.079
Something you're reluctant
to repeat.

09:39.112 --> 09:42.015
Funny thing, I didn't even
see Vivian yesterday.

09:42.049 --> 09:44.718
There was a huge,
exhausting medical emergency,

09:44.752 --> 09:46.219
which is why I
fell asleep early,

09:46.253 --> 09:47.821
which explains everything. Bye.

09:49.823 --> 09:51.792
(sighs)

09:51.825 --> 09:57.297
Okay, uh, Lavon, you'll do
your mayoral champagne toast,

09:57.330 --> 09:59.232
applause, applause, applause.

09:59.266 --> 10:00.367
Then I will

10:00.400 --> 10:01.735
introduce the Belles,

10:01.769 --> 10:03.370
who will then sing
an original number.

10:03.403 --> 10:05.238
Why are they late to rehearsal?

10:05.272 --> 10:07.240
I don't stand for divas.

10:07.274 --> 10:09.276
Crickett texted me.
They're on their way.

10:09.309 --> 10:10.410
CRICKETT:
Update.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.346
We have arrived!

10:15.148 --> 10:17.718
Where are the rest
of 'em?
DASH:
Ladies,

10:17.751 --> 10:21.054
might I remind y'all that
rehearsal is mandatory?

10:21.088 --> 10:23.123
Oh. Oh, we're not here
to rehearse.

10:23.156 --> 10:26.059
(plays note)

10:26.093 --> 10:28.395
* You showed up drunk
on A.B.'s door *

10:28.428 --> 10:31.398
* You basically called her
Gainey's whore *

10:31.431 --> 10:33.701
* Well, you won't get away
with that no more *

10:33.734 --> 10:35.135
* So there'll be no Belles

10:35.168 --> 10:37.037
* At the Toast and Roast

10:37.070 --> 10:38.839
* So suck it...

10:38.872 --> 10:40.107
* Lavon

10:40.140 --> 10:42.309
* Hayes.

10:51.218 --> 10:52.385
O-Okay, uh,

10:52.419 --> 10:53.721
d-don't worry about this.

10:53.754 --> 10:55.188
Heh. I'll fix it.

10:55.222 --> 10:57.157
(chuckles,
clears throat)

10:57.190 --> 10:58.425
(indistinct chatter)

10:58.458 --> 11:00.193
MAN:
That was just rude.

11:00.227 --> 11:02.763
(band playing foxtrot music)

11:04.197 --> 11:05.365
Mae?

11:05.398 --> 11:08.435
Lemon.
What are you doing here?

11:08.468 --> 11:11.772
(sighing): Well... I was
worried about you, Mae.

11:11.805 --> 11:13.073
When you came
to Fancie's earlier,

11:13.106 --> 11:14.842
you weren't
your usual self.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.244
You were missing
your pep, your zest,

11:17.277 --> 11:20.080
your joie de vivre,
so I brought pie.

11:20.113 --> 11:21.381
(laughing):
Joie de vivre pie?

11:21.414 --> 11:22.883
Is this about that A-minus?

11:22.916 --> 11:25.452
(chuckles) It's not
the grade I care about.

11:25.485 --> 11:28.321
(foxtrot music continues)
It's the, uh... credibility

11:28.355 --> 11:29.790
of the system.

11:29.823 --> 11:31.458
What is that music?

11:31.491 --> 11:33.293
That's the sound of
my broken dreams.

11:33.326 --> 11:35.462
Not enough pie in the
world to fix 'em.

11:35.495 --> 11:37.097
Oh, Mae, I knew
it must have been something.

11:37.130 --> 11:37.998
Sweetie, tell me.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.433
Well, I just spent
the last six months

11:40.467 --> 11:43.203
rehearsing for a ballroom
dance competition tonight,

11:43.236 --> 11:45.505
until my partner tore
his Achilles tendon.

11:45.538 --> 11:46.940
I didn't want to win.

11:46.974 --> 11:48.742
I just wanted to
compete, you know?

11:48.776 --> 11:51.311
Like that character in that
movie who just wants to dance.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.914
Black Swan?
 The Company? Step Up?

11:53.947 --> 11:55.949
Shall We Dance?
 Step Up 2?

11:55.983 --> 11:58.451
Dance With Me? Take the Lead?
 Strictly Ballroom?

11:58.485 --> 12:01.354
Silver Linings
 Playbook?
Third one, I think.

12:01.388 --> 12:03.891
*
What if I told you

12:03.924 --> 12:06.326
that I happen to know
an excellent ballroom dancer

12:06.359 --> 12:08.128
who's available this evening?

12:08.161 --> 12:10.931
I guess... I would
have to ask...

12:10.964 --> 12:12.766
does he have good hygiene?

12:12.800 --> 12:15.468
I mean, once a health inspector,
always a health inspector.

12:15.502 --> 12:18.238
As a matter of fact,
he is a doctor.

12:18.271 --> 12:20.908
I know this medication
is helping me,

12:20.941 --> 12:23.811
but I think
it's making me crazy.

12:23.844 --> 12:26.279
One second,
I'm so happy.

12:26.313 --> 12:28.849
I look at Tom,
I love him so much.

12:28.882 --> 12:30.517
The next,

12:30.550 --> 12:34.855
I see his eyebrows,
and they are so bushy.

12:34.888 --> 12:38.191
I want to tear those
eyebrows out, like rip
them off his face!

12:38.225 --> 12:40.293
But moodiness is a common
side effect of Clomiphene.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.394
Now the good news:

12:41.428 --> 12:43.163
it is working!

12:43.196 --> 12:46.266
You are officially
ovulating.

12:46.299 --> 12:48.568
So you and Tom need to start
trying to make

12:48.601 --> 12:50.403
a baby tonight.
(chuckles)

12:50.437 --> 12:52.806
Bushy eyebrows or not.
(quiet laugh)

12:52.840 --> 12:54.307
(bell tinkles)

12:55.308 --> 12:57.310
Hey.

12:57.344 --> 13:00.313
AnnaBeth, could you
do me a small favor?
If Wade happens to ask,

13:00.347 --> 13:03.350
can you say there was a medical
emergency yesterday afternoon?

13:03.383 --> 13:04.584
You want me to lie to Wade?

13:04.617 --> 13:06.319
Exactly. Also,
if he calls or drops by,

13:06.353 --> 13:08.288
can you tell him that
I'm in with a patient?

13:08.321 --> 13:10.991
Also a lie. Wanda's
the only patient

13:11.024 --> 13:13.393
on the books, and she
is already in with Brick.

13:13.426 --> 13:16.029
What? Brick needs a consult?
I'll be right in.

13:16.063 --> 13:17.564
Oh, hey, Wade.

13:17.597 --> 13:19.432
I hope you're not sick,
'cause sadly,

13:19.466 --> 13:20.700
there's a situation
with a patient.

13:20.733 --> 13:23.904
Brick and I are probably gonna
be in with her a-all morning.

13:23.937 --> 13:26.840
A-All day.
Maybe into night.

13:26.874 --> 13:29.843
Did you hear about
that big medical
emergency yesterday?

13:29.877 --> 13:31.444
Because, boy,
it was very big,

13:31.478 --> 13:32.545
very...

13:32.579 --> 13:34.314
medical.

13:34.347 --> 13:35.883
Hmm.

13:35.916 --> 13:37.918
Dr. Hart, what are...
what are you?
Oh, well,

13:37.951 --> 13:39.252
Wanda's my patient, too,

13:39.286 --> 13:41.021
and I also care about
her future offspring.

13:41.054 --> 13:42.622
How is the
Clomiphene going?

13:42.655 --> 13:46.559
It's making me crazy,
but it's working.
Yeah.
Hey,

13:46.593 --> 13:49.529
that's great!
Now, now, I'm just
gonna let Wanda go home

13:49.562 --> 13:51.965
and get ready
for baby-making tonight.

13:51.999 --> 13:54.467
Home? No.
We should talk first.

13:54.501 --> 13:56.336
Have a nice long talk,

13:56.369 --> 13:57.938
you know,
about positions and timing,

13:57.971 --> 14:00.340
getting Tom to relax,
getting him in the mood.

14:00.373 --> 14:03.944
What? You think I can't
get Tom in the mood?

14:03.977 --> 14:05.946
Well, I most
certainly can!

14:05.979 --> 14:08.281
Why do you
think I can't?
No. Nothing. No reason.

14:08.315 --> 14:09.582
Good! 'Cause I can!

14:11.284 --> 14:13.320
Thank you for your
input, Dr. Hart.

14:13.353 --> 14:14.654
That was very helpful.

14:14.687 --> 14:16.957
Yes, Sergeant Jeffries
was bitten by an anaconda.

14:16.990 --> 14:18.391
Hmm.
But luckily, Dr. Hart

14:18.425 --> 14:20.093
was there
to stitch him up.
Oh.

14:20.127 --> 14:21.461
WANDA:
Anacondas?

14:21.494 --> 14:22.462
In BlueBell?

14:22.495 --> 14:25.532
What kind of place is this
to raise a child?!

14:25.565 --> 14:27.334
(Wanda sobbing)

14:27.367 --> 14:28.668
Hey,

14:28.701 --> 14:29.937
Doc.

14:29.970 --> 14:31.972
You know, AnnaBeth was actually

14:32.005 --> 14:33.974
just telling me
about the big emergency.

14:34.007 --> 14:35.408
See, I didn't realize

14:35.442 --> 14:37.377
we've got anacondas
here in Alabama.

14:37.410 --> 14:40.380
ANNABETH:
Uh, that's right, we don't.

14:40.413 --> 14:42.415
It must have escaped
from the zoo.

14:42.449 --> 14:44.317
That explains it!
Very likely story.

14:44.351 --> 14:45.986
Thank you, AnnaBeth.
(weak chuckle)

14:47.487 --> 14:49.089
I can't tell you.

14:49.122 --> 14:51.591
Zoe, please,
you've got to tell me.

14:53.460 --> 14:55.562
LulaBelle, why
don't you tell George

14:55.595 --> 14:58.631
about your summer working
as a counselor at Bible camp?
Oh, wow.

14:58.665 --> 15:01.601
Wow, Sunday school
teacher all year round,
and Bible camp

15:01.634 --> 15:03.937
in the summer--
that is so, uh...

15:03.971 --> 15:06.539
"Devout" is the word
that you're looking for.

15:06.573 --> 15:08.008
That is. That is the word

15:08.041 --> 15:10.310
I was looking for.
George also

15:10.343 --> 15:12.412
spent a summer working in
Bible camp. Didn't you?

15:12.445 --> 15:14.381
I did. I did.

15:14.414 --> 15:16.716
I also found it
to be extremely

15:16.749 --> 15:20.520
enlightening and,
uh, and-and whatnot.

15:20.553 --> 15:23.356
Hey, here's an idea.
Why don't you two kids

15:23.390 --> 15:26.159
go out for a nice dinner
and share war stories?

15:26.193 --> 15:28.395
Yeah! You
talk it over.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.497
The reverend is gonna help
me make another pot of tea.

15:30.530 --> 15:32.432
(laughs): No, sweetheart,
you don't need two people

15:32.465 --> 15:33.566
to make a pot of...

15:33.600 --> 15:35.535
Yes, you do need
two people.

15:35.568 --> 15:37.037
GEORGE: So...

15:37.070 --> 15:39.672
(clears throat, chuckles)

15:39.706 --> 15:42.609
Uh, so, about tonight...

15:42.642 --> 15:44.677
Pick me up at 7:00.
Drop me off around the corner.

15:44.711 --> 15:47.514
I'll tell the Mayfairs we
went for burgers and bowling.

15:47.547 --> 15:48.781
No one'll be the wiser.

15:48.815 --> 15:51.618
Are you blowing me off?
No offense,
but anyone who thought

15:51.651 --> 15:55.388
Bible camp was "enlightening"
just is not my type.
Well,

15:55.422 --> 15:57.690
uh, I am sitting here,
having tea and crumpets

15:57.724 --> 16:00.693
with the reverend and his wife.
(brief chuckle)

16:00.727 --> 16:03.063
What exactly
would you like me to say?

16:03.096 --> 16:05.465
So you lied
to a man of the cloth

16:05.498 --> 16:08.068
in his own home,
over his own tea and crumpets?

16:08.101 --> 16:10.537
I am a little bit more
complicated than I seem.

16:10.570 --> 16:12.139
We'll have to see about that.

16:12.172 --> 16:13.606
I was gonna try
this new club

16:13.640 --> 16:15.642
in Montgomery tonight.
You want to join?

16:15.675 --> 16:18.411
You know, I am looking
for a distraction,

16:18.445 --> 16:20.147
so yes, why the hell not?

16:20.180 --> 16:21.748
ZOE:
 Vivian's my cousin,

16:21.781 --> 16:23.083
Wade-- I promised.

16:23.116 --> 16:24.617
But you want
to tell me.

16:24.651 --> 16:25.718
I can see that.

16:25.752 --> 16:27.420
Yes.
So if you
can't speak,

16:27.454 --> 16:29.422
maybe you can... blink.

16:29.456 --> 16:32.559
All right? Like, one blink
for no, two blinks for yes.

16:34.127 --> 16:37.097
Why aren't you saying anything?
You in or out?

16:37.130 --> 16:38.631
Well, I was blinking.
I just blinked twice.

16:38.665 --> 16:40.567
Oh. Oh, oh, all right.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.735
So... was I right?

16:42.769 --> 16:45.172
Is Charles trying
to win Vivian back?

16:47.740 --> 16:49.209
(gulps)

16:49.242 --> 16:52.779
And is...
is she considering him?

16:56.116 --> 16:57.750
You got something
in your eye, Doc?

17:04.223 --> 17:06.093
Wade, where
are you going?

17:07.160 --> 17:08.694
(groans)

17:08.728 --> 17:09.762
(knocking)

17:11.263 --> 17:12.499
Lavon.

17:12.531 --> 17:14.501
Look, I-I get that
you're still mad at me

17:14.534 --> 17:16.069
and it's probably
gonna take a while

17:16.103 --> 17:18.105
for you to forgive me,
if ever. That's fair.

17:18.137 --> 17:20.807
But considering how
small this town is,
could you try

17:20.839 --> 17:23.210
and resist turning the Belles
against me, too?

17:23.242 --> 17:25.278
I'm sorry,
you think I did what now?

17:25.311 --> 17:27.547
The Belles dropped out
of the Mayoral Toast and Roast.

17:27.579 --> 17:29.282
You're the leader
of the Belles.

17:29.316 --> 17:31.084
(laughing):
Oh, my God.

17:31.118 --> 17:34.087
You'd think a couple of days
could go by without you

17:34.121 --> 17:37.524
blindly accusing me of
sabotaging the town of BlueBell?

17:37.557 --> 17:38.825
I see.

17:38.858 --> 17:41.094
So this is not you punishing me?

17:41.128 --> 17:43.596
No. You did that
all on your own,

17:43.630 --> 17:45.498
with your ridiculous
and childish

17:45.532 --> 17:47.500
and very un-mayoral behavior.

17:47.534 --> 17:48.768
Okay, you know what?

17:48.801 --> 17:51.538
I came here to apologize, again.

17:51.571 --> 17:53.140
Try and make peace.

17:53.173 --> 17:54.507
Forget it.

17:55.542 --> 17:57.644
Yeah, you know what?
The-the Mayoral

17:57.677 --> 18:00.313
Toast and Roast will-will do
just fine without the Belles.

18:00.347 --> 18:02.182
Yeah, we will sell
plenty of tickets

18:02.215 --> 18:03.716
without your dumb song.

18:03.750 --> 18:06.219
Oh! Well, that is
really good to hear,

18:06.253 --> 18:09.722
because the Belles
are about to be

18:09.756 --> 18:12.559
very busy preparing
for a new tradition.

18:12.592 --> 18:15.262
The first ever annual

18:15.295 --> 18:17.730
Head-of-the-Belles
Toast and Roast.

18:17.764 --> 18:18.865
What?

18:18.898 --> 18:20.233
But there is no...

18:20.267 --> 18:22.169
Oh, you can't do that.

18:22.202 --> 18:23.903
Oh, I just did.
Oh, and guess what.

18:23.936 --> 18:25.872
It happens to be
on the same night.

18:25.905 --> 18:27.340
(gasps): Oh!
See you, Lavon.

18:27.374 --> 18:28.741
(door slams)

18:28.775 --> 18:30.310
(grunts)

18:31.911 --> 18:34.781
(thunder crashes)

18:36.783 --> 18:38.685
Of course.

18:42.222 --> 18:44.123
(knocking)

18:45.925 --> 18:47.794
Zoe told you.

18:47.827 --> 18:48.795
Yeah.

18:48.828 --> 18:51.631
Wade... I'm so sorry.
No, let me

18:51.664 --> 18:53.666
talk first, all right?
I got something to say.

18:53.700 --> 18:55.335
I get what being

18:55.368 --> 18:56.736
with Charles means, all right?

18:56.769 --> 18:59.239
You got a son
and you got history.

18:59.272 --> 19:02.242
But you and me, w-we got
something real right now.

19:02.275 --> 19:05.912
And I'm not gonna stand by and
let him take you away from me.

19:05.945 --> 19:07.380
I-I can't do that.

19:08.848 --> 19:10.850
That is the most...

19:10.883 --> 19:13.152
romantic thing I've ever heard.

19:27.267 --> 19:28.935
*

19:28.968 --> 19:30.937
(whistling)

19:30.970 --> 19:32.372
Well, hello there, Doc.

19:32.405 --> 19:33.806
You're up early.

19:33.840 --> 19:35.375
It is a glorious day,

19:35.408 --> 19:37.277
is it not?
Where have you been?

19:37.310 --> 19:39.646
Well, a gentleman
doesn't kiss and tell.

19:39.679 --> 19:41.314
But because
I am no gentleman...
Hmm.

19:41.348 --> 19:42.915
I was at Vivian's.

19:42.949 --> 19:44.917
Oh, really?
So you talked?
Mm-hmm.

19:44.951 --> 19:47.820
Put it all on the line.
Told her I wouldn't
give up without a fight.

19:47.854 --> 19:50.423
And then she
took me in her arms...

19:50.457 --> 19:53.326
like in one of those
movies you like so much.

19:53.360 --> 19:55.295
Wade, that's amazing.
Well,

19:55.328 --> 19:57.297
the better man won.
Well, so when's

19:57.330 --> 19:59.799
she gonna talk to Charles?
I don't know.
I don't care.

19:59.832 --> 20:01.868
But she did say she
was gonna talk to him?

20:01.901 --> 20:04.804
Well, I mean, not
in so many words.
But it was

20:04.837 --> 20:07.407
strongly implied
by her lack of clothing.

20:07.440 --> 20:08.708
Hmm?
Okay.

20:08.741 --> 20:11.878
Look, we had
an incredible night last night.

20:11.911 --> 20:13.780
And if you're saying

20:13.813 --> 20:15.948
(chuckles):
that... I mean, after we...

20:15.982 --> 20:17.850
and...

20:17.884 --> 20:20.753
th-th-that she
would choose him...

20:20.787 --> 20:21.988
W... I'm not saying anything.

20:22.021 --> 20:24.991
Look, I just hope that you're
not jumping to conclusions,

20:25.024 --> 20:26.959
hearing things that
weren't actually said.

20:28.695 --> 20:31.298
Look, I-I don't want to put you
in an awkward position,

20:31.331 --> 20:34.334
but maybe you could, uh...
you can just talk to her.

20:34.367 --> 20:36.035
All right?
Put in a good word for me.

20:36.068 --> 20:38.738
She trusts you.
Okay.

20:38.771 --> 20:41.441
Zoe Hart! All right!
Hey, you want to head over

20:41.474 --> 20:43.009
to Lavon's? If he's
making waffles,

20:43.042 --> 20:44.677
I'm buying.

20:44.711 --> 20:46.012
All right, well,
let's do it. Come on.

20:46.045 --> 20:47.647
I got your
little mag here.

20:47.680 --> 20:50.049
It's a newspaper!
A newspaper, Wade.
Oh, yeah.

20:50.082 --> 20:54.354
Without the Belles,
this Toast and Roast is toast.

20:54.387 --> 20:56.055
If they're putting on
their own show,

20:56.088 --> 20:57.657
who's gonna want
to watch us?

20:57.690 --> 20:59.459
I don't even know
what we're doing here.

20:59.492 --> 21:01.761
I got 19 episodes
of Chicago Fire

21:01.794 --> 21:04.331
burning up my DVR.

21:04.364 --> 21:05.498
We all done crying
in our soup?

21:05.532 --> 21:06.833
Oh, come on, Lavon,
you got to admit,

21:06.866 --> 21:08.735
things are looking mighty bleak.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.837
No. No, I don't.

21:10.870 --> 21:12.805
And you know why?

21:12.839 --> 21:14.407
'Cause I'm talking
to the BlueBell Owls.

21:14.441 --> 21:16.476
Okay, look,
maybe

21:16.509 --> 21:18.711
our legs won't look as good
in a cancan line

21:18.745 --> 21:20.046
as the Belles.

21:20.079 --> 21:21.047
But we got something else.

21:21.080 --> 21:22.782
It's gonna be that kind of show?

21:22.815 --> 21:24.050
Like a Full Monty type thing?

21:24.083 --> 21:25.952
What? No!

21:25.985 --> 21:28.388
Look, I'm talking
about what we got right here.

21:28.421 --> 21:29.989
I am sitting here

21:30.022 --> 21:32.692
with the most talented
musical men of this generation.

21:32.725 --> 21:34.361
Now, who's with me?

21:34.394 --> 21:36.028
(grumbling)

21:36.062 --> 21:36.829
I don't know, Lavon.

21:37.497 --> 21:40.533
Stanley.

21:40.567 --> 21:43.069
I saw you channel Fred Astaire
in Shelby's cabaret.

21:43.102 --> 21:45.405
Oh, yeah, he did, yeah.
Huh? At least from
the knees down.

21:45.438 --> 21:48.074
And, Frank,
Bill, Wally,

21:48.107 --> 21:49.075
y'all harmonize

21:49.108 --> 21:50.843
like the best barbershop
quartet,

21:50.877 --> 21:52.412
and there's only three of you.

21:52.445 --> 21:53.346
Yeah, that's true.
Huh?

21:53.380 --> 21:54.547
That's true.

21:54.581 --> 21:55.915
And, Reverend,

21:55.948 --> 21:58.418
