24:13.920 --> 24:16.523
but I figure we only have
a few hours to rehearse.

24:16.556 --> 24:18.558
Mae, this is my daddy, Brick.

24:18.591 --> 24:20.560
Daddy, this is
Mae Ellen Waterloo,

24:20.593 --> 24:23.229
your dance partner
for this evening.
Wow.

24:23.262 --> 24:26.599
That is a
spectacular gown.

24:26.633 --> 24:29.001
And you are exactly
the right height.
Oh.

24:29.035 --> 24:30.169
(chuckles)
This is...

24:30.202 --> 24:32.004
a dream come true.
(chuckles)

24:32.038 --> 24:32.972
How's your feather step?

24:33.005 --> 24:35.608
Well, in a hyphenated word,

24:35.642 --> 24:36.976
award-winning.

24:37.009 --> 24:39.111
Oh. Good.
(chuckles)

24:39.145 --> 24:40.513
(squeals)

24:42.582 --> 24:43.650
(knocking)

24:44.684 --> 24:46.653
Oh, there she is,

24:46.686 --> 24:48.955
the Edward Snowden
of family secrets.

24:48.988 --> 24:50.122
I am so sorry.

24:50.156 --> 24:51.591
Come in.

24:54.694 --> 24:57.597
Zoe, I-I put you
in a terrible position.

24:57.630 --> 24:59.065
I don't blame you at all.

24:59.098 --> 25:01.167
What is going on?

25:01.200 --> 25:04.671
As you may have heard,
Wade and I had the most

25:04.704 --> 25:06.238
incredible night.
And he was...

25:06.272 --> 25:08.541
romantic and strong...

25:08.575 --> 25:10.009
I don't...
I don't need the details.

25:10.042 --> 25:12.278
But that is great.
Yay, Wade! Right?

25:12.311 --> 25:14.914
But this morning
Charles came by.

25:14.947 --> 25:16.683
And he got
a job offer

25:16.716 --> 25:18.184
in Baton Rouge.

25:18.217 --> 25:19.686
He wants to move.

25:19.719 --> 25:21.287
Wow.

25:21.320 --> 25:23.189
Wait, Charles is going
to Baton Rouge?

25:23.222 --> 25:25.625
That's gonna be hard on Harley.

25:25.658 --> 25:27.627
Oh, no, no.
Zoe, you don't understand.

25:27.660 --> 25:30.029
This is a huge job.

25:30.062 --> 25:32.031
He wants all of us to move.

25:32.064 --> 25:33.933
Charles thinks
that this...

25:33.966 --> 25:35.568
could be our clean slate,

25:35.602 --> 25:37.003
a fresh start.

25:37.036 --> 25:40.206
But, Vivian, you don't love
Charles anymore.

25:40.239 --> 25:42.008
I mean, you've moved on.

25:42.041 --> 25:44.043
But here's the thing.
Uh, the other night,

25:44.076 --> 25:46.078
when he told me
that he still had feelings,

25:46.112 --> 25:49.048
he...
kissed me.

25:49.081 --> 25:51.017
And I kind of...

25:51.050 --> 25:52.284
I kissed him back.

25:52.318 --> 25:55.154
Oh, Vivian.
I know. But we were
high school sweethearts

25:55.187 --> 25:56.355
and he was
my husband.

25:56.388 --> 25:58.157
We have a child together.

25:58.190 --> 26:00.126
Those feelings
just don't go away.

26:00.159 --> 26:01.694
But what about Wade? You know?

26:01.728 --> 26:03.696
(phone ringing)
He's a good guy. He deserves...

26:03.730 --> 26:04.731
Excuse me.

26:04.764 --> 26:07.133
Hey, Winifred, what's up?

26:07.166 --> 26:09.268
(sighs)
Oh, my God.

26:09.301 --> 26:11.070
No, no. Yeah,
I-I'll be right there.

26:11.103 --> 26:14.273
Harley fell off the jungle gym.
He may have a broken arm.

26:14.306 --> 26:15.708
I'll drive.

26:22.081 --> 26:24.583
(sighs, moans)

26:26.085 --> 26:27.353
(exhales)

26:27.386 --> 26:29.321
Psst, Tom.

26:29.355 --> 26:31.057
Mayor Hayes?

26:31.090 --> 26:32.191
I've been leaving you messages,
man.

26:32.224 --> 26:35.061
I turned my phone off.
I have a big night ahead of me.

26:35.094 --> 26:37.229
Wanda says cellular devices
transmit stress.

26:37.263 --> 26:39.766
I am not to be stressed.
O-Okay,

26:39.799 --> 26:41.233
but I need to talk to you
about doing the lights

26:41.267 --> 26:42.635
for the Mayoral Toast and Roast.

26:42.669 --> 26:45.204
Turns out, through a quirk
in the calendar,

26:45.237 --> 26:47.840
the Belles' show is the exact
same night as the Owls'.

26:47.874 --> 26:51.711
Oh, that's gonna put me
in an uncomfortable position.

26:51.744 --> 26:53.345
You know how everybody loves
your lighting design.

26:53.379 --> 26:54.714
ANNABETH:
 We are willing to give you

26:54.747 --> 26:56.382
above-the-title credits.

26:56.415 --> 26:59.085
"Tom Long presents the Head
of the Belles Dinner."

26:59.118 --> 27:01.153
They're talking about making you
an honorary Owl.

27:01.187 --> 27:03.255
For life.
 U-Unlimited babysitting

27:03.289 --> 27:06.258
for baby goats or any humans
that come along.

27:06.292 --> 27:07.526
LAVON:
 You know, I-I'll be okay.

27:07.559 --> 27:11.263
But the rest of the guys will be
very disappointed if you say no.

27:11.297 --> 27:12.799
Very disappointed.

27:12.832 --> 27:15.234
I don't want to upset anyone.
 Well,

27:15.267 --> 27:17.236
then you know what to do.
Because the Belles

27:17.269 --> 27:20.272
would consider it the mother
of all slaps in the face.
So what do you say?

27:20.306 --> 27:22.074
I need an answer, Tom!
(groans)

27:22.108 --> 27:24.711
I-I need some time
I need some time

27:24.744 --> 27:26.746
to think about it.
to think about it.

27:28.380 --> 27:29.415
(grunts)

27:29.448 --> 27:31.851
WOMAN (over P.A.):
 Dr. Kravitz, you have a visitor

27:31.884 --> 27:33.185
in the main lobby.

27:33.219 --> 27:34.286
VIVIAN:
Harley,
sweetie,

27:34.320 --> 27:35.755
are you okay, baby?

27:35.788 --> 27:37.156
Mommy, I fell.

27:37.189 --> 27:40.259
I feel horrible.
I looked away for one second.

27:40.292 --> 27:42.161
It's not your fault.
Things happen.

27:42.194 --> 27:43.696
Buddy, you okay?

27:43.730 --> 27:45.698
Daddy, my arm hurts. My face

27:45.732 --> 27:48.267
is bleeding.
Okay, big guy.

27:48.300 --> 27:49.769
We're gonna sew up
that chin and take

27:49.802 --> 27:51.170
some cool pictures of the inside

27:51.203 --> 27:53.305
of your arm.
I know what an X ray is.

27:53.339 --> 27:55.141
Good for you.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.744
Mom, Dad, one of you want
to come be my assistant?

28:00.379 --> 28:02.381
(foxtrot music playing)

28:17.496 --> 28:19.398
Big finish!

28:21.400 --> 28:22.401
(song ends)
(Lemon yelps)

28:23.469 --> 28:25.872
(both laugh)

28:25.905 --> 28:27.807
Oh, you just...

28:27.840 --> 28:29.308
We're actually good.
It was like

28:29.341 --> 28:30.810
riding a bicycle.

28:30.843 --> 28:33.479
Oh, Mae, you know,
if-if I can survive the evening,

28:33.512 --> 28:35.347
we may do some damage
at this contest.

28:35.381 --> 28:36.182
(laughing):
My gosh.

28:36.215 --> 28:38.150
(phone ringing)
Oh, I better get that.

28:38.184 --> 28:39.351
Uh, don't forget
to hydrate.

28:39.385 --> 28:41.788
Okay.

28:41.821 --> 28:44.190
Well? Someone has got

28:44.223 --> 28:47.326
her sparkle back. Now, that
is the Mae I remember.

28:47.359 --> 28:49.361
Y'all are gonna set
that dance floor on fire.

28:49.395 --> 28:52.398
Yeah, well, hold that thought.
Oh, no.

28:52.431 --> 28:54.300
BRICK:
Mae, I am so sorry to do
this to you. That was

28:54.333 --> 28:57.403
a medical emergency, and I...
I have to attend to it.

28:57.436 --> 29:01.240
But you... you do such
a beautiful box step.

29:01.273 --> 29:02.875
I-I do wish I could go,

29:02.909 --> 29:06.145
'cause I think we could kick
some serious ballroom butt.

29:06.178 --> 29:07.914
(chuckles)
Unfortunately,

29:07.947 --> 29:09.949
duty calls.

29:13.853 --> 29:15.254
That stinks.

29:16.255 --> 29:17.824
Don't despair, Mae.

29:17.857 --> 29:19.358
I have an idea.

29:21.527 --> 29:22.862
(loud whisper):
Tom?

29:22.895 --> 29:25.231
Tom, I got your message.

29:25.264 --> 29:26.398
Tom.

29:26.432 --> 29:28.868
Where are you, man?

29:28.901 --> 29:30.336
Oh, I don't believe this.

29:30.369 --> 29:32.304
Let me guess.
Y-You got a text from Tom,

29:32.338 --> 29:34.406
and it said he had come
to a decision

29:34.440 --> 29:36.208
regarding the lights and...

29:36.242 --> 29:39.211
We should rendezvous at the
gazebo? Yep. Same text.

29:39.245 --> 29:40.412
I think someone's messing
with us.

29:40.446 --> 29:42.448
WANDA:
Good guess, Sherlock.

29:43.449 --> 29:44.817
Wanda?

29:44.851 --> 29:47.486
Yep. Just Wanda.

29:47.519 --> 29:49.421
Disappointing, huh?

29:49.455 --> 29:53.292
How does it feel to show
up somewhere with such

29:53.325 --> 29:56.028
high hopes only to find out

29:56.062 --> 29:58.430
you're not gettin'
what you expected?

29:58.464 --> 30:00.232
Wanda, what's going on?

30:00.266 --> 30:02.935
Are you wearing fishnets?
Yes, I am!
'Cause tonight's

30:02.969 --> 30:05.304
a big night for me and Tom,

30:05.337 --> 30:08.540
a big, big, big night,

30:08.574 --> 30:10.309
which is why
Tom was relaxing

30:10.342 --> 30:12.511
until you two ding-dongs undid
all my doing.

30:12.544 --> 30:15.915
And, hello,
now Tom's so stressed

30:15.948 --> 30:19.585
about who he's supposed to help,
he can't... perform.

30:19.618 --> 30:21.587
Well, guess what.

30:21.620 --> 30:23.489
If he can't perform,

30:23.522 --> 30:27.259
you don't perform.

30:27.293 --> 30:29.561
It was his fault!
It's her fault!

30:29.595 --> 30:31.063
Do I look like I care?

30:31.097 --> 30:32.598
Shut up

30:32.631 --> 30:35.067
and come fix my husband!

30:36.068 --> 30:37.469
Oh...

30:38.504 --> 30:40.272
Hey.

30:40.306 --> 30:41.874
I spoke to the
radiologist,

30:41.908 --> 30:43.375
and Harley's arm
isn't broken.

30:43.409 --> 30:44.576
Oh, thank God.

30:44.610 --> 30:46.412
(chuckles)
Uh, look,

30:46.445 --> 30:48.080
I get how it must look to you.

30:48.114 --> 30:50.082
Okay? I'm the dad
who left his family

30:50.116 --> 30:51.450
and now I want back in.

30:51.483 --> 30:52.919
Look, I don't know you.

30:52.952 --> 30:55.654
But I care about Vivian
and I care about Wade.

30:55.687 --> 30:57.556
And you can't keep just playing

30:57.589 --> 30:59.358
with people's feelings
like this.
No,

30:59.391 --> 31:00.326
I'm not playing.

31:00.359 --> 31:02.628
I've never been more serious
about anything.

31:02.661 --> 31:05.297
Vivian, she's my true love.

31:05.331 --> 31:07.466
All right? All I want to do
is make her remember

31:07.499 --> 31:09.668
how good things were
and can be again.

31:09.701 --> 31:11.603
And I know you and Wade
are close.

31:11.637 --> 31:13.472
And he's a good guy.

31:13.505 --> 31:16.008
But we're a family
and we deserve another chance.

31:17.009 --> 31:19.111
WINIFRED:
Oh, hey.

31:19.145 --> 31:22.514
That's right.
I bought a guilt gift.

31:22.548 --> 31:23.983
And I bought
doughnuts.

31:24.016 --> 31:25.651
What's going on with you two?

31:25.684 --> 31:26.652
Nothing.

31:26.685 --> 31:27.519
No.

31:27.553 --> 31:28.587
Come on. Let's sit.

31:30.990 --> 31:33.960
Lemon?

31:33.993 --> 31:35.962
I think I'm gonna go.

31:35.995 --> 31:38.464
Tell your dad thanks for trying.

31:38.497 --> 31:41.000
LEMON:
Wait!

31:41.033 --> 31:43.535
*

31:46.538 --> 31:48.007
That is so sweet.

31:48.040 --> 31:49.408
(giggling)

31:49.441 --> 31:50.409
I don't think
it'll work, though.

31:50.442 --> 31:52.711
I mean, neither one of us
knows how to lead.

31:52.744 --> 31:55.581
Oh, honey, speak for yourself.

31:55.614 --> 31:57.984
*

32:00.086 --> 32:03.122
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Dr. Kravitz, you have a visitor
in the main lobby.

32:03.155 --> 32:05.124
Daddy, I had stitches!

32:05.157 --> 32:07.526
Oh. Come here,
my brave guy.

32:07.559 --> 32:08.961
Oh!

32:08.995 --> 32:10.162
Just glad
you're all right.

32:10.196 --> 32:11.463
I love you.

32:11.497 --> 32:12.598
I love you, too.

32:12.631 --> 32:14.600
VIVIAN:
My, don't forget about me.

32:14.633 --> 32:16.502
Yeah. Let me
see. Lift up?

32:16.535 --> 32:18.037
Yeah.
That hurt?

32:18.070 --> 32:19.071
No, not
anymore.

32:19.105 --> 32:20.072
Oh, real
tough guy.

32:20.106 --> 32:21.507
Huh?
VIVIAN:
Very.

32:21.540 --> 32:23.509
(laughter)

32:23.542 --> 32:25.577
CHARLES:
We got to get him back out
on the diamond.

32:25.611 --> 32:26.979
You should see him hit a ball...
VIVIAN:
Maybe let's not...

32:27.013 --> 32:28.080
Are you okay?

32:28.114 --> 32:30.049
Oh, yeah.

32:30.082 --> 32:32.084
(indistinct chatter)

32:32.118 --> 32:35.554
Could you just...
tell them that I had to go?

32:43.129 --> 32:45.164
(laughs)
Amazingness.

32:45.197 --> 32:47.133
Kicked out of two
clubs in one night.

32:47.166 --> 32:49.001
Yeah, see,
that's gonna happen when

32:49.035 --> 32:51.103
you insist on calling a bouncer
"Tiny" repeatedly.

32:51.137 --> 32:52.504
That's...
(laughter)

32:52.538 --> 32:55.641
Bouncers-- you know, just
no appreciation for irony.

32:55.674 --> 32:57.676
At all. None.

33:00.479 --> 33:02.481
Tequila makes me hungry.

33:02.514 --> 33:04.616
Where can a girl
get a snack?

33:04.650 --> 33:07.086
Well, miss, it is
your lucky night,

33:07.119 --> 33:08.754
because I happen
to know a gentleman

33:08.787 --> 33:10.756
who owns half a restaurant.

33:10.789 --> 33:12.158
Really?
Yeah.

33:12.191 --> 33:13.692
Come on.

33:13.725 --> 33:15.027
I just don't
know what to do.

33:15.061 --> 33:16.495
I mean, it's right
there in the Bible.

33:16.528 --> 33:18.130
"Let there be light." But it
doesn't say who gets the light.

33:18.164 --> 33:19.765
Lavon, A.B.-- they're both
my friends, but I don't...

33:19.798 --> 33:22.101
Tom. Tom, Tom,
you are babbling again.

33:22.134 --> 33:23.769
Now, think about
the calming ocean

33:23.802 --> 33:26.572
and waves lapping
on the shore.

33:26.605 --> 33:27.706
Can you hear that?

33:27.739 --> 33:30.142
I do. I do.
Of course, now I have

33:30.176 --> 33:32.244
to pee.
Oh.

33:32.278 --> 33:34.580
Look at him!
Look at what y'all did!

33:34.613 --> 33:36.448
Wanda, yelling is
counterproductive.
Sorry.

33:36.482 --> 33:38.717
It's not me. It's
my ovaries yelling.

33:38.750 --> 33:41.220
Hey, buddy.
How we doing?

33:41.253 --> 33:43.122
Work faster!

33:43.155 --> 33:44.356
Okay, uh, listen
to me, Tom.

33:44.390 --> 33:46.525
I don't want you to worry
about the lights anymore, okay?

33:46.558 --> 33:48.227
Go and do the
Belle Show.
No, no,
do the Owl show.

33:48.260 --> 33:49.528
Another choice?

33:49.561 --> 33:50.662
What if maybe...

33:50.696 --> 33:52.131
We combine our shows

33:52.164 --> 33:53.232
and-and we do 'em together?

33:53.265 --> 33:54.600
Maybe we do them outside

33:54.633 --> 33:55.767
during the day,
and we won't

33:55.801 --> 33:56.802
even need lights at all!

33:56.835 --> 33:58.170
So, now you don't
want my lights?

33:58.204 --> 33:59.571
Okay.
ANNABETH:
No, no, no.

33:59.605 --> 34:01.240
We love... we love
your lights. Um, we just...

34:01.273 --> 34:02.574
We don't want you
to be concerned.

34:02.608 --> 34:03.842
LAVON:
Right. The only spotlight

34:03.875 --> 34:06.145
you should be worried
about is the one

34:06.178 --> 34:08.547
that you're gonna
use... to make a baby.

34:08.580 --> 34:09.715
BRICK:
What?

34:09.748 --> 34:11.449
Ew, Lavon.

34:11.483 --> 34:14.085
No. That worked.

34:15.286 --> 34:17.456
Okay, good enough for me.

34:17.489 --> 34:19.525
I love y'all,
but everybody out!

34:19.558 --> 34:20.626
Oh.

34:20.659 --> 34:22.094
Now!

34:27.733 --> 34:29.201
You know I love you.

34:29.235 --> 34:31.770
I do. I... Mm.

34:31.803 --> 34:34.172
Mmm.

34:34.206 --> 34:36.208
(goat bleats)

34:37.743 --> 34:39.545
Out!

34:40.879 --> 34:43.282
(sighs)

34:43.315 --> 34:44.683
(whooping)

34:44.716 --> 34:45.884
Ah!

34:45.917 --> 34:47.619
Ah!

34:47.652 --> 34:50.255
(humming)

34:50.289 --> 34:51.723
(laughter)

34:51.757 --> 34:53.259
Seventh place!

34:53.292 --> 34:54.726
It's a miracle.

34:54.760 --> 34:55.827
I know.

34:55.860 --> 34:57.229
Oh, Lemon,

34:57.263 --> 34:58.630
I can't thank you enough.

34:58.664 --> 35:00.199
Tonight has been

35:00.232 --> 35:02.534
a dream come true.

35:02.568 --> 35:04.736
I only hope one day
I can return the favor.

35:04.770 --> 35:05.871
Well,

35:05.904 --> 35:09.241
now that you mention it,
you could reinspect Fancie's.

35:09.275 --> 35:10.776
Sure. Let's do it.

35:10.809 --> 35:12.744
Really? But it's after midnight.

35:12.778 --> 35:14.346
I'll never be in a happier mood.

35:14.380 --> 35:17.183
Well... let's go.

35:17.216 --> 35:18.717
Okay, come on.

35:20.586 --> 35:21.753
(playing gentle melody)

35:21.787 --> 35:22.888
(knocking)

35:22.921 --> 35:25.724
Hey.

35:25.757 --> 35:27.626
Hey, Doc. Where you been?

35:27.659 --> 35:28.760
The hospital.

35:28.794 --> 35:30.329
Harley fell off the jungle gym.

35:30.362 --> 35:32.764
But he's okay.
He just needed some stitches.

35:32.798 --> 35:34.233
Geez Louise, poor kid.

35:34.266 --> 35:36.335
Uh, you know, I should...
I should call Viv.

35:36.368 --> 35:38.270
You know what? They're...
They're probably exhausted.

35:38.304 --> 35:40.239
Right. Yeah, yeah.

35:40.272 --> 35:42.841
Hey, uh, did you...
did you have a chance

35:42.874 --> 35:44.710
to put in a word for me?

35:44.743 --> 35:46.912
I didn't.
Okay, well, uh,

35:46.945 --> 35:48.547
no rush, I guess.

35:48.580 --> 35:52.651
Actually, Wade, I don't think
there's much of a point.

35:52.684 --> 35:54.386
What do you mean?

35:54.420 --> 35:56.688
(clears throat)

35:56.722 --> 35:58.290
Okay, look,

35:58.324 --> 36:00.359
I'm your friend,

36:00.392 --> 36:03.195
so that's why I think
this should come from me.

36:03.995 --> 36:06.832
I don't see this
turning out for you.

36:07.966 --> 36:11.169
Charles and Vivian
are getting back together.

36:11.970 --> 36:14.340
No.

36:14.373 --> 36:18.277
No, I mean, Viv-Viv and I--
we-we have... we have something.

36:18.310 --> 36:19.811
We have something real.

36:19.845 --> 36:21.813
No, I-I'm sure you do.

36:21.847 --> 36:24.283
Just, Charles is moving away,

36:24.316 --> 36:26.785
and eventually
Vivian's going to go with him.

36:26.818 --> 36:28.820
You know, Wade, I saw them
all together tonight...

36:28.854 --> 36:30.289
Wow. You know, uh,

36:30.322 --> 36:32.591
on second thought, Zoe,

36:32.624 --> 36:35.394
I... I don't think
I need your help anymore.

36:36.862 --> 36:38.830
Excuse me.

36:39.865 --> 36:41.867
Wade.

36:44.270 --> 36:46.272
(door slams)

36:48.674 --> 36:50.242
It already
looks great.
Oh. (laughs)

36:50.276 --> 36:52.644
No condiments left on
the tables, unrefrigerated.

36:52.678 --> 36:53.745
(laughs)

36:53.779 --> 36:55.247
(clinking)

36:55.281 --> 36:57.283
What was that?

36:57.316 --> 36:59.951
(dishes and glassware
clattering and clinking)

36:59.985 --> 37:01.853
Sounds like some
kind of animal.

37:01.887 --> 37:02.954
(laughs)

37:02.988 --> 37:06.292
No, trust me, there are
no animals in this restaurant.

37:08.360 --> 37:10.662
GEORGE:
You're gonna get it now.

37:10.696 --> 37:12.364
LULABELLE:
Stop it! Get away! Don't do it!

37:12.398 --> 37:13.799
GEORGE (laughing):
Oh, you are gonna get it now.

37:13.832 --> 37:14.966
If you do it,
I'm gonna get you back then.

37:15.000 --> 37:16.435
I'm gonna get you.
You are gonna get it.

37:16.468 --> 37:18.036
You are gonna get it.
I am. Watch this.

37:18.069 --> 37:19.838
GEORGE: Are you kidding me?
LULABELLE:
No, I'm not. Stop.

37:19.871 --> 37:21.006
You are gonna get it.
(laughing)

37:21.039 --> 37:23.742
I'm gonna get you.
(laughing)

37:23.775 --> 37:26.278
(chuckles softly)

37:26.312 --> 37:27.979
I stand corrected.

37:28.013 --> 37:31.483
Whipped cream, anyone?

37:40.025 --> 37:42.361
Dr. Breeland, Wanda and
I just wanted to say

37:42.394 --> 37:44.363
thank you for your
help last night.

37:44.396 --> 37:45.864
Well, it's not
your typical house call,

37:45.897 --> 37:47.032
but I am here to serve.

37:47.065 --> 37:50.035
The visualizing
helped quite a bit.

37:50.068 --> 37:51.903
This mind is a
very powerful tool.

37:51.937 --> 37:53.038
(laughs)

37:53.071 --> 37:54.373
Very powerful.

37:54.406 --> 37:55.240
WANDA:
Dr. Breeland doesn't want

37:55.273 --> 37:57.909
to hear about your tools
over breakfast.

37:57.943 --> 38:00.379
Anyway, hope to be
seeing a lot more of you

38:00.412 --> 38:01.747
in the next nine months.

38:01.780 --> 38:03.349
Fingers crossed.

38:05.417 --> 38:06.818
Hmm.

38:07.986 --> 38:11.957
Uh, look, A.B., I know I
apologized about being a jackass

38:11.990 --> 38:15.394
about your new boyfriend,
but I also know

38:15.427 --> 38:16.962
that I wouldn't have
accepted my apology either.

38:16.995 --> 38:18.830
I stepped over the line.

38:18.864 --> 38:21.066
I wish I hadn't.

38:21.099 --> 38:24.002
But I-I hope that we
can be friends again.

38:24.035 --> 38:26.338
I guess we kind of have to,

38:26.372 --> 38:28.874
if only for the sake
of the town, right?

38:33.412 --> 38:36.348
LulaBelle tells me she had
a great time last night.

38:36.382 --> 38:39.084
She also said y'all managed
to get in some Bible study.

38:39.117 --> 38:40.386
Is that true?

38:40.419 --> 38:42.053
She wouldn't lie
to a man of the cloth.

38:42.087 --> 38:43.154
Would she? We-we had a...
a great time,

38:43.188 --> 38:45.457
and I wanted to thank you
for the introduction.
Mm.

38:45.491 --> 38:48.427
'Cause, as it turns out,
a-a little bit of, uh,

38:48.460 --> 38:50.929
Bible study is-is
all I needed.

38:50.962 --> 38:52.097
Well, that's a good thing,

38:52.130 --> 38:54.466
'cause that sheep
you were talking about?

38:54.500 --> 38:56.368
She's...
(à la sheep): baaack!

38:57.869 --> 38:59.871
Our new health inspection
report came in.

38:59.905 --> 39:02.741
You want to guess
what we got?

39:02.774 --> 39:04.109
We got a "C," George!

39:04.142 --> 39:05.176
A "C" for
health, thanks

39:05.210 --> 39:07.813
to you and your culinary
debauchery in the kitchen!

39:07.846 --> 39:09.915
I had to sweet-talk
her out of an "F"!

39:09.948 --> 39:11.883
Well, that's... I mean,
well, that's good news.

39:11.917 --> 39:12.984
(laughing):
Silver linings.

39:13.018 --> 39:14.119
Oh, you think
that this is funny?!

39:14.152 --> 39:16.422
No.
Then why are
you smiling?

39:16.455 --> 39:18.424
(laughing):
Because I...

39:18.457 --> 39:21.393
I am highly annoyed
with you right now.

39:21.427 --> 39:22.928
That's all I am feeling

39:22.961 --> 39:25.497
is a... is a very high level
of annoyance.

39:25.531 --> 39:26.898
La-dee-dee-da and
happy day for you.

39:26.932 --> 39:28.867
George, you own that "C."
That "C" is all your fault.

39:28.900 --> 39:30.035
And you better start thinking

39:30.068 --> 39:31.136
about how you're gonna
raise that grade.

39:31.169 --> 39:33.472
Will do, Lemon. I got it.

39:33.505 --> 39:34.606
George, where are you going?

39:34.640 --> 39:37.476
I am not done with you yet.

39:37.509 --> 39:38.944
(knocking)

39:40.078 --> 39:41.112
What are you doing here?

39:41.146 --> 39:42.481
What are you doing here?

39:42.514 --> 39:44.015
Didn't Vivian call you?

39:44.049 --> 39:45.484
Yeah, she left a
message, said to call.

39:45.517 --> 39:46.918
I figured I'd just
stop by in person.

39:46.952 --> 39:48.454
Oh, God.

39:48.487 --> 39:51.056
Hey, Viv?

39:52.991 --> 39:55.160
Wade, Vivian--

39:55.193 --> 39:59.030
she went away for the
weekend... with Charles.

39:59.064 --> 40:01.032
They're looking for
houses in Baton Rouge,

40:01.066 --> 40:03.602
and I'm watching Harley
while she's gone.

40:03.635 --> 40:05.971
Went out of town with Charles?

40:07.639 --> 40:09.841
No. No way. I don't believe you.

40:09.875 --> 40:11.076
I'm so sorry.

40:13.211 --> 40:15.180
You're sorry?

40:15.213 --> 40:18.183
You could have stopped this.
She would have listened to you.

40:18.216 --> 40:19.618
That is not fair, Wade.

40:19.651 --> 40:21.086
What was I supposed to do?

40:21.119 --> 40:23.088
One favor, Zoe.

40:23.121 --> 40:25.090
I asked you one favor.

40:25.123 --> 40:27.225
After everything
we've been through.

40:27.258 --> 40:28.627
But I saw
what you were up against,

40:28.660 --> 40:29.895
and it wouldn't have worked.

40:29.928 --> 40:31.630
No, no, that wasn't
your call to make!

40:31.663 --> 40:33.499
Shh.

40:33.532 --> 40:35.534
Hey, Wade.

40:35.567 --> 40:37.536
Hey.

40:37.569 --> 40:39.237
Hey,

40:39.270 --> 40:40.906
little buddy.

40:40.939 --> 40:43.008
Uh... wow.

40:43.041 --> 40:45.043
Look at those
stitches.

40:45.076 --> 40:47.946
I, uh... I got you something.

40:47.979 --> 40:50.115
Whoa!

40:50.148 --> 40:52.083
It's just like yours?

40:52.117 --> 40:54.553
Yeah, remote control and
everything. Hope you like it.

40:54.586 --> 40:57.022
Awesome. Thank you.

40:57.055 --> 40:59.224
Hey,

40:59.257 --> 41:00.592
did you hear?

41:00.626 --> 41:02.193
We're moving to Baton Rouge.

41:03.595 --> 41:06.598
Wow.

41:06.632 --> 41:09.134
Yeah. Yeah,
you know, that's...

41:09.167 --> 41:10.235
that's a great place.

41:10.268 --> 41:11.937
I think you'll really like it.

41:11.970 --> 41:13.104
Yeah.

41:13.138 --> 41:15.006
Um... you know,

41:15.040 --> 41:17.008
I should... I should...
I should get going.

41:17.042 --> 41:18.610
So, uh,

41:18.644 --> 41:22.180
I'll see you later, all right?

41:22.213 --> 41:24.115
All right.
All right.

41:24.149 --> 41:26.151
Yeah.
